\tThe American Civil War has ended, with the Union Armies surrendering to the victorious Confederate Armies!\n\tConfederate field commanders report Union soldiers laying down their weapons. This victory confirms the Confederate States of America as an independent nation among nations, free to choose its own destiny.\n\tThe President of the Confederate States has called for a Grand Review of the Armies in the Confederate capital city. This grand display of the South𠏋 victorious forces on parade will fill the city full of amazed citizens to cheer the troops and the hard fought victory they achieved.\n\tThe President of the United States of America is humiliated, his support is wavering and the disgruntled population of the North demands that he stand down.\n\tThe Grand Herald congratulates the victorious troops of the Confederacy. With the War over, it's time to think about the future. What will become of the Americans of the two nations?
