508
Lincoln Calls for Volunteers!
\tThe President of the United States Abraham Lincoln, has called for the formation of a militia, 75,000 strong. The militia will be formed of volunteers from across the nation and will serve for three months. The volunteers are to bolster the numbers of the U.S. Army that is preparing to fight the Confederacy.\n\tIn the South this call has been denounced as an act of war against the sovereign southern states. The citizens are aroused to resist against what they call unprovoked northern aggression.\n\tIn Arkansas, Tennessee, Virginia, North Carolina, Missouri and Kentucky the politicians are dismayed by Lincoln's orders and are refusing to form militias to fight their brethren. Whilst these states previously voted to remain in the Union, now secession conventions are being held in them. Any state that secedes will be welcomed with open arms by the Confederate States. While some states may initially declare to be independent or neutral, in the event that full scale fighting were to flare up it seems unlikely that they could remain as a neutral bystander.
