31
A Great Union Victory!
\tFinally, a major field battle has been fought between the inexperienced armies of the Union and the Confederacy. In this battle the Union troops prevailed and they now hold the field having sent the rebels running for their lives.\n\tThis news is welcomed with enthusiasm in Washington D.C. President Lincoln calls it a great achievement on the road to the inevitable victory and offers his thanks to all of the men who fought in the battle. Union support is reportedly strong and it is believed to be only a matter of weeks or months before the Confederacy is defeated in detail and the Union restored.\n\tIn the South the population is in shock after the Confederate troops lost heart, turned and ran. While their situation is turning desperate, morale of the citizens remains high and the military leadership is declaring they will continue the desperate fight for independence, whatever the odds.
