A Great Confederate Victory!
\tFinally a major field battle has been fought between the inexperienced armies of the Union and the Confederacy. In this battle the Confederate troops have prevailed and they now hold the field having sent the Yankees running for their lives.\n\tThe news is welcomed with enthusiasm in the Confederacy. President Davis calls it a great achievement on the road to the inevitable victory and offers his thanks to all the men who fought in the battle. Confederate support is reportedly strong and the citizens believe the northern armies can be beaten and independence gained.\n\tIn the North, the population is in shock after the Union troops lost heart, turned and ran. Lincoln is quoted as saying: "It's bad, it's damn bad". Already many are questioning his leadership and in are coming out in favor of a political compromise.
