20
The Republican Party Won the Elections.
\tThe House of Representative elections are over, and the Republican Party maintained the majority in the House. President Lincoln can sleep assured that he has the support of his party in the war effort. While Democratic support has been strong and vocal for the past years, it's clear that the people of the United States stand united behind Lincoln.\n\tMany of the so called "Copperheads", or Democrats in support of Peace with the Confederacy, have lost their seats in the Congress. Among them is Ohio representative Clement Vallandigham, a possible future presidential candidate, who has opposed every military bill.\n\tThe Confederates saw these elections as a great opportunity to undermine Lincoln. Their efforts to demoralize the Union citizens have failed, inaction is not an option, the Confederates will need decisive victories.
