32
Democrats Gain Majority!
\tThe Democratic Party won the House of Representatives elections and now hold the majority in the House. This election may be a decisive moment in the war as the citizens have clearly shown their disapproval for President Lincoln's war effort against the Confederacy.\n\tThe Democratic Party is not unanimous about how to handle the crisis, but it's clear that they will stand against Lincoln's policy. Many believe the Democrats will eventually support peace negotiations with the Confederates. Whether this is true or not, it's clear that the policy making in the U.S. will soon be in turmoil.\n\tAlready we can see the Union population losing faith in their leaders. If the Union wishes to win the war, they must press on before the remaining support for the war is completely lost.
