6
Union has Captured 10 Forts.
\tUnion armies have been victorious against Confederate defenses. The static fieldworks and fortifications that were supposed to stop any northern advances into Confederate lands have been rendered useless by the glorious Union armies, they stormed the parapets and forced the garrisons to surrender.\n\tThe citizens welcome the news and cheer, Union pride and morale has received a significant boost. The people are confident that the troops in blue will emerge victorious from this war and that the southern rebellion will be utterly crushed.\n\tIn the South the defensive plans have had to be completely revised with the fall of so many important fortifications. Retaking them should be a priority and many generals vow to take decisive action, however the people have started questioning the ability of their armies to protect their homes and lands from the successful Union armies.
