540
The Western part breaks away from the State of Virginia.
\tThe recent campaigns in Western Virginia and the Kanawha Valley have been a great success for the Union armies, they now control this mountain region and all of its important towns. With the Confederate forces removed from the area the local citizens, who mostly support the Union and voted against secession in early 1861, are preparing to form a new independent state loyal to the Union. But what will the name be? Kanawha, Allegheny, Augusta, Columbia, New Virginia, Vandalia perhaps? What best describe the state, formed of the Western part of Virginia?\n\tGeographically this is a stinging blow to the Confederacy. Whilst mountainous and a difficult terrain to support armies in, West Virginia offered them a route to undertake operations in the upper Shenandoah Valley. The benefits of the region𠏋 mining industry will now go to the Union.
