34
Union in Control of the Mississippi River!
\tUnion military operations along the Mississippi river have been successful and all the major ports along America's greatest waterway have fallen to their armies. This success is widely celebrated in northern cities, it's recognized as being a major milestone on the road to victory.\n\tGeneral Winfield Scott designed the Anaconda plan in 1861 to strangle the Confederacy. Holding New Orleans, Baton Rouge, Vicksburg and Memphis allows Union river squadrons, troops and supplies to be moved rapidly to engage any Confederate troops in Louisiana, Mississippi or Arkansas. It also allows the opening of new fronts along other major waterways.\n\tThe news is received with great dismay in the South as the Confederacy has effectively been cut in half with no further hope of mutual support between the two. 
