Union defeats Queen Victoria.
\tThe British have suffered a stinging defeat in combat with the Union military. While the intervention was seen as a great opportunity to humiliate their old enemy, it is the world's largest empire that finds itself humiliated.\n\tThe northern citizens are ecstatic about the recent news, with patriotic tunes played and the cracking of fireworks heard throughout the night in many major cities. The British intervention seems to be losing steam and already our reporters in London hear of plans to withdraw from the conflict after the defeat.\n\tThe British army was struggling in the Crimea a decade ago and it seems the rigid military traditions have not allowed the army to transform enough to be effective in modern combat. It's more than likely, that this will spark others to challenge their authority around the world.
