541
Lincoln Defeated!
\tLincoln has lost the presidential elections of 1864! His opponent, a famous general from the Union Officer Corps has convinced the northern people that Lincoln's handling of the crisis has been a failure. With a Democratic president taking the office in March 1865, it's believed that support for the war will continue to diminish. The people are tired of the war and want a change.\n\tIn the Confederacy, politicians and people alike cheer as the news reaches the major cities. With Lincoln forced to step down, it's likely that the United States will finally agree to enter negotiations about ending the war. Already the fragile political unity in Washington has been compromised and the loud voices in favor of ending the fighting are gaining momentum.\n\tThe only way to avoid a complete humiliation is for Lincoln to defeat the Confederates militarily before the spring, before national morale collapses completely.
28
