Union Casualties Reach New High!
Confederate Armies Stand Firm!
Political Support in Union Wavering!
Number of Volunteers Diminishing!
Union Citizens Demoralized!
33
Union Losses Becoming Unacceptable.
\tThe Union casualties have reached shocking new heights in futile fighting with Confederate armies. The high number of casualties has rocked Union citizens, who eagerly await the end of the war. However the Union generals keep committing their men in unwinnable battles with losses that result in much grief around the nation.\n\tAnti war sentiment has been gaining ground, with support for the war reaching a new low point, the people are tired of war. With no victories on the horizon, the Union armies could find themselves losing soldiers to desertion than can be replaced by recruitment. The Confederacy policy to bleed the life from the Union armies may yet force northern politicians to negotiate peace.
