Shenandoah Campaign a Success!
Union Controls the Valley!
Winchester Falls!
CSA Lost its Bread Basket!
Panic in Confederate Congress!
537
Union Forces Control the Strategically Important Valley.
\tThe recent campaign up the Shenandoah Valley has left the strategically important corridor firmly in Union hands. As Union controls the Valley, troops and supplies can move fairly protected from Potomac up the Valley.\n\tThe Valley was important to Confederate war-effort in many ways. The fertile valley was able to feed large armies. It also allowed a covered line of advance to cut the Union's life line to the west, namely Baltimore & Ohio Railroad and canal system, and to bypass Washington D.C.'s defences from the west.\n\tNow, with the Valley under Union control, the opposite is true. The troops in blue are able to threaten cutting Virginia of from the Western Theater, or to turn the flank of the defences in the east.
