Baltimore & Ohio Cut!
CSA Controls the Lower Valley!
Cumberland Falls!
Union's Lifeline to West Lost!
Panic in U.S. Congress!
535
Confederate Advance Cuts Baltimore & Ohio Railroad.
\tBaltimore & Ohio Railroad connects the eastern states of the Union to Ohio and the west. The railroad runs from Baltimore, through the northern tip of Virginia, via Grafton in western Virginia to Wheeling. Alongside runs canals that together with the rail line provide a strategically important life line to Union's coordinated war-effort.\n\tThe recent Cofnederate campaign has been able to capture the vital chokepoint of this lifeline. With the gray-clad troops controlling Hagerstown and Cumberland in Maryland, Union can no longer use its most important railroad connection to Ohio. All goods must now be taken through a more rugged line further north through Pennsylvania, which has much lower capacity.\n\tThis turn of events has the Union leadership in disarray. Military commanders are blamed for the disaster, while the political leadership is said to be behind the lack of success due to lack of supporting the military.
