Confederate Forces Captured Hagerstown and Frederick.
\tMaryland, the border state that surrounds Washington D.C., has been loyal to the Union since the war started, protecting the U.S. capital from all directions but south. With the recent successful offensive operation by the Confederacy, Maryland is effectively cut in half.\n\tThe situation is untenable for the Union, and all effort is being placed in operations to recapture the lost terrain. Failing to do so will have a severe impact on Union's capacity to fight, as the CSA has a freedom of movement and action in Maryland and into Pennsylvania.
