Confederate Forces Advance up to Harrisburg.
\tAn unstoppable Confederate offensive has penetrated deep into Pennsylvania. Following the Cumberland Valley Railroad, the attack has captured a line from Hagerstown all the way to Harrisburg. This attack has effectively cut the Union in half, even if movement of troops and supplies is still possible further north.\n\tThe Union leadership is total chaos. Military leadership is blamed for lack of effort to contain the Confederate offensive in the first place. All efforts are being diverted to capture back the lost ground, but in the current turmoil it seems questionable if the Union armies can manage such task.\n\tIn the south, citizens are ecstatic and cheering their grey-clad heroes. With such success, there seems to be no way that the Confederacy could lose this war.
