Union Forces Have Established a Firm Foothold in North Carolina Coast.
\tIn recent operations Union forces have established a firm foothold in the North Carolina coasta by capturing towns of New Bern and Plymouth. This has severly disrupted Confederate sea trade and movement of supplies north along the coast, and secured a base for further operations in North Carolina Union forces.\n\tConfederate forces are reported consolidating further inland and most likely preparing to re-capture the towns. What remains to be seen, is whether a counter-attack will ever materialize, as the Confederate leadership is in state of confusion regarding where to place the main effort of future campaigns.
