67
Union Forces have Captured Norfolk and the Gosport Shipyard.
\tWhen Virginia joined the Confederate States of America they demanded the surrender of all Federal property in their state, including the Gosport Shipyard. Falling for an elaborate Confederate ruse orchestrated by civilian railroad builder, William Mahone, the Union shipyard commander Charles Stewart McCauley ordered the burning of the shipyard and the evacuation of its personal to Fort Monroe across Hampton Roads. The capture of the shipyard allowed a tremendous amount of war material to fall into Confederate hands including the remains of the burned and scuttled naval frigate USS Merrimac.\n\tNow, Union forces have returned and re-captured this strategically important shipyard. Doing so, Confederate trade has also been dealt a great blow. The Confederate government is in turmoil after this critical loss.
